In all the various recent comments about the ANC/Cuba relationship (Cover Story, April 14-20) there appears to be one aspect that has been overlooked. Many now accept the ANC habit of conflating its  interests with those  of the nation. But surely the relationship with Cuba is an ANC-only matter, as that political party benefited from it and,  arguably, the nation as a whole did not? Why should SA  taxpayers have paid — and continue to pay — many millions for that relationship instead of the ANC? Robert StoneLinden The FM welcomes concise letters from readers. They can be sent to fmmail@fm.co.za